To iterate all subsets of a string `s`, we can use bit twiddling to generate all possible combinations of the indices of the characters of `s`. 

Here's the code:

```
String s = "abc";
int n = s.length();

for (int i = 0; i < (1 << n); i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
        if ((i & (1 << j)) != 0) {
            System.out.print(s.charAt(j));
        }
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```

In the above code, we iterate over all possible integer values between `0` and `(1 << n) - 1` (inclusive) using the outer loop. For each integer value `i`, we check the binary representation of `i` and print the characters corresponding to the set bits of `i`.

